Reasoning: The paper deals with communication complexity of linear algebraic problems, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for efficient communication among multiple players (message passing model). The focus is on lower bounds (cs.CC) for problems such as determining matrix rank, computing entries in its inverse, and solving linear equations. The paper also considers related problems such as computing the generalized inner product of vectors held on different servers, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses promise problems, which are a common topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
